text:
Students should choose boarding places based on safety, cleanliness, distance to campus, and cost.
They should check water, electricity, internet availability, and nearby transport facilities.
Always visit the place before paying any advance.
Talk with current residents and neighbors to understand the environment.

Students should prepare a monthly budget including food, transport, rent, printing, and internet.
Track daily expenses using a notebook or mobile app.
Avoid unnecessary spending and save at least 10% of income.
Review and adjust the budget every month.

Active participation in clubs, societies, and events helps students build confidence and friendships.
Maintaining good relationships with lecturers and classmates improves academic success.
Balancing academics with social life reduces stress and improves overall well-being.

Students should identify career goals early and work on required skills.
Building a strong CV and LinkedIn profile is essential.
Internships and part-time jobs provide valuable real-world experience.
Communication skills and teamwork are important for career success.

Common student expenses include food, transport, rent, printing, internet, and study materials.
Tracking expenses helps identify unnecessary costs.
Cooking meals and using student discounts can reduce monthly expenses.

Students should eat balanced meals with fruits, vegetables, protein, and enough water.
Avoid excessive fast food consumption.
Maintaining healthy eating habits improves energy, focus, and academic performance.

Students can earn income through part-time jobs, tutoring, freelancing, and online work.
Managing income wisely helps avoid financial stress.
Saving a portion of earnings is important for future needs.

Mental health is important for academic success.
Students should manage stress through proper planning, regular exercise, good sleep, and social support.
Talking with friends, family, or counselors helps maintain emotional well-being.

Students can earn online through freelancing, content writing, graphic design, programming, video editing, and tutoring.
Websites like Fiverr, Upwork, and Freelancer provide job opportunities.
Building skills increases earning potential.

Part-time jobs help students gain experience and earn money.
Balancing part-time work with studies is essential to avoid academic stress.
Jobs in tutoring, retail, and campus services are suitable for students.

Effective study includes active recall, spaced repetition, and regular revision.
Creating a daily study schedule improves consistency.
Studying in focused sessions (Pomodoro technique) increases productivity.

Students should plan transport routes to minimize cost and travel time.
Using public transport and season tickets reduces expenses.
Walking or cycling for short distances improves health and saves money.
